<br>
You've been misled into believing the Court used the right of privacy, by itself, in this decision.  Actually, they grounded their decision in the 14th Amendment Equal Protection Clause as well as the right to privacy.  This lends it a lot more Constitutional weight than if it were simply grounded in the right to privacy found in Griswold and Roe v. Wade.<br>
<br>
The Roemer decision (Colorado case) was also grounded in the 14th Amendment Equal Protection Clause.<br>
<br>
Further, it's extremely significant that they said Bowers v. Hardwick was &quot;never correct&quot;.  The only other time they've invalidated a decision with such strong language was with Brown v. Board. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=robingoodfellow>Robin Goodfellow</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://home.earthlink.net/~andersonrob/RAINBO~1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1404<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/27/03 9:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm62.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=527.topic&index=28>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: It's about time... sodomy laws declared unconstitutional</span><hr size=1> My error.  It's the 5th &amp; 14th Amendment Due Process Clause the Court relied upon. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=twotribes>Twotribes</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Troll</span><br>  Posts: 863<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/27/03 11:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm62.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=527.topic&index=29>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: It's about time... sodomy laws declared unconstitutional</span><hr size=1> The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter Day Saints, Mormon for those that dont know it, hasnt recognized pologamy since the late 1890's. People that practice it and claim to be &quot;mormon&quot; arent part of the main church, they are fringe dwellers that have ignored the church and want to keep the 